# TypeScript Standards

## Type safety
- No `any` — use `unknown` + narrow, or define explicit type
- No `as Foo` type assertions without runtime verification
- No `!` non-null assertion — use `?.` and `??`
- Explicit return types on all exported functions

## Functions
- Max 50 lines per function (prefer ≤ 30)
- Max 5 parameters (use options object if more)
- Max 3 nesting levels (use early return to flatten)
- No `console.log` in production — use project logger

## Imports
- External packages first, then `src/` imports, then relative
- No barrel `index.ts` that creates circular deps
- Named exports over default exports on React components

## Error handling
- Never swallow: `catch (e) {}` — handle, rethrow, or log with context
- Async functions: return `Result<T, E>` or throw typed error class
- `try/catch` at service boundaries, not inside tight loops

## Tests
- Colocate tests: `utils.ts` → `utils.test.ts`
- No `test.only` or `describe.only` (silently skips others in CI)
- Coverage target: 80% on new features
